description: Borrowed from Spanish taco (“light lunch”, literally “stopper, plug, wad”).

entries.meaning: (cooking) A Mexican snack food made of a small tortilla (soft or hard shelled) filled with ingredients such as meat, rice, beans, cheese, diced vegetables and salsa.
(US, slang) A yellow stain on a shirt armpit caused by sweat or deodorant.

verbs.description: taco (third-person singular simple present tacos, present participle tacoing, simple past and past participle tacoed)

entries.meaning: (slang) To fold or cause to buckle in half, similar to the way a taco is folded.
